germany 's trade surplus hit a 10-month high in june as imports fell at a faster rate than exports .
seasonally adjusted imports dropped by 4.5 % , the biggest fall since january 2009 , while exports slid 2.8 % , according to the federal statistics office .
the trade surplus rose to 21.2bn euros in june from 20.3bn the month before .
the wider current account measure , which also includes investment flows , recorded a surplus of 23.6bn euros , up from may 's surplus of 16bn euros .
germany has been criticised for the size of its current account surplus .
the international monetary fund has said germany should boost investment and increase imports to help boost growth in other countries .
